The paper discusses the topic of place recognition from a computer vision and robotics perspective, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of traditional image retrieval techniques and convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely candidates.
